<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-pricing-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How our accounting pricing works.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>We price accounting services one way: a <code>fixed fee</code>, scoped to your file and put in writing before any work starts. After a short discovery call and a review of your books, you get a single flat figure &mdash; a fixed monthly fee for ongoing bookkeeping, or a flat project fee for a cleanup or a fresh setup &mdash; along with exactly what it covers. There is no hourly meter running in the background and no surprise invoice at month-end. You decide with the number in front of you.</p>
      <p>We scope rather than publish one flat price because two businesses with the same revenue can have very different books: one with a few dozen transactions a month and a single account, another with high volume, payroll, sales tax, inventory, and multiple entities. A single posted price would either overcharge the simple file or under-serve the complex one. So the fee reflects the real drivers of <em>your</em> books &mdash; and once it&rsquo;s agreed, it holds for that scope. If your needs change later, we re-scope and agree a new fixed fee in writing before anything changes. This page is the accounting-silo view; the <a href="/pricing/">main pricing page</a> shows the full picture across everything we do.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-pricing-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
