<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-pricing-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How we price</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">One written fixed fee, scoped to your file.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The discipline behind the fee is simple: look before we quote, then quote a flat figure that holds. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications reviews your file &mdash; transaction volume, accounts, payroll, sales tax, inventory, entity structure, and how current the books are &mdash; maps it onto the canonical ranges, and puts a single fixed fee in writing with exactly what it covers. No hourly meter, no surprise invoice, and a re-scope (also in writing) only if your needs change. The fee is ours, set for the operational accounting work inside your own books &mdash; not Intuit, and separate from any QuickBooks subscription Intuit bills you for. For a free look before you talk price, <a href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review">get the free file review</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

